data.title: Slipknot Kick Off 25th Anniversary Tour: Here's What They Played
data.meta_description: 'Nothing you are about to hear tonight was written after 1999!'
data.text:
Slipknot kicked off their 25th anniversary North American tour on Tuesday night (August 6) in Noblesville, Indiana and treated fans to a throwback set of 1999-era material.

“Nothing you will hear tonight was written after 1999,” singer Corey Taylor told the crowd, as the band donned their old-school red jumpsuits and era-appropriate masks. Slipknot is celebrating the 25th anniversary of their 1999 self-titled album (their first with Taylor) and played a 14-song setlist featuring fan-favorites and deep cuts including “No Life” and set closer “Scissors," which they haven't played live since 2000.

Slipknot will traverse the country this summer and fall, including a stop in their home state of Iowa for the star-studded Knotfest. The tour is also notable, as the band's playing with their recently revealed new drummer Eloy Casagrande. Although they're celebrating old material, the metal icons have also teased a new song called "Long May You Die," which they recorded with Casagrande.

Watch fan-footage of "No Life" and "Scissors," and check out Slipknot's full setlist below.
